ABa.doc: Set to false if you don't want invoices to be sent to your customers

ABu.doc: Currency in which amount is set. Allowed values are NGN, GHS, ZAR or USD

ABw.doc: Number of invoices to raise during subscription to this plan. Set to 0 for infinity.

ABy.doc: Amount should be in kobo if currency is NGN, pesewas, if currency is GHS, and cents, if currency is ZAR

ACA.doc: Interval in words. Valid intervals are: daily, weekly, monthly,biannually, annually.

ADn.doc: If customer has multiple authorizations, you can set the desired authorization you wish to use for this subscription here. If this is not supplied, the customer's most recent authorization would be used

ADx.doc: Set the date for the first debit. (ISO 8601 format) e.g. 2017-05-16T00:30:13+01:00

AED.doc: Customer's email address or customer code

AEZ.doc: Amount should be in kobo if currency is NGN, pesewas, if currency is GHS, and cents, if currency is ZAR

AEa.doc: Unique case sensitive transaction reference. Only -,`.`, = and alphanumeric characters allowed. If not specified, a reference will be auto-generated for the transaction

AEb.doc: The transaction currency (NGN, GHS, ZAR or USD). Defaults to your integration currency.

AEc.doc: Fully qualified url, e.g. https://example.com/ where customer will be redirected to after payment.

AEe.doc: If transaction is to create a subscription to a predefined plan, provide plan code here. This would invalidate the value provided in amount

AEf.doc: The split code of the transaction split. e.g. SPL_98WF13Eb3w

AEg.doc: The code for the subaccount that owns the payment. e.g. ACCT_8f4s1eq7ml6rlzj

AEh.doc: An amount used to override the split configuration for a single split payment. If set, the amount specified goes to the main account, and the rest goes to the subaccount.

AEi.doc: Who bears Paystack charges? account or subaccount (defaults to account).

AEl.doc: Amount should be in kobo if currency is NGN, pesewas, if currency is GHS, and cents, if currency is ZAR

AEm.doc: Valid authorization code to charge e.g AUTH_nopw9k1we

AEn.doc: Unique case sensitive transaction reference. Only -,`.`, = and alphanumeric characters allowed. If not specified, a reference will be auto-generated for the transaction

AEo.doc: Currency in which amount should be charged. Allowed values are: NGN, GHS, ZAR or USD

AEp.doc: The code for the subaccount that owns the payment. e.g. ACCT_8f4s1eq7ml6rlzj

AEq.doc: An amount used to override the split configuration for a single split payment. If set, the amount specified goes to the main account, and the rest goes to the subaccount.

AEr.doc: Who bears Paystack charges? account or subaccount (defaults to account).

AEs.doc: The split code of the transaction split. e.g. SPL_98WF13Eb3w
